Andy:

I remember your name from the past.  I started the Read_Alphabet group
after having used QS for 25+ years because I felt those of us who favor
QS over Shavian needed a forum to develop the QS resources available on
the net.  Unfortnately, I have so many demands on my time, that I have
not been able to devote the time to the group that I would like to.

We still need an improved version of Jerome (font) to communicate in.
Jon Zuck did a great job getting us started, but Jerome still has some
problems that need to be addressed

I am using a hybrid Linux/Windows OS, and have not worked out how to use
Jerome or a version thereof on my Linux box yet, which in the past few
months has kept me from sending messages on the site using QS.

Ewout introduced us to the use of a program called Keyman to let us
remap our keyboards to type QS, including its half-letters.  I prepared
a key mapping, based upon Jon Zuck&#39;s and my own ideas, which is
predicated upon some of the traditional roman alphabet orthography.
This  makes typing in QS much easier than the desparately unintuitive
mapping the Shavian group uses.   I sent a couple of e-mails about this
back in late winter or early spring but received no feedback so I have
no idea if anyone in the group besides myself is using this presently.

Good to hear from you again.

Paige Gabhart

